$ SQL: select first row only

Different database products have different SQL clauses to → development/databases/SQL/select[select] the first row or the first n rows only.
  • → development/databases/Oracle 12c has the → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/select/first-n-rows#ora-sql-row-limiting-clause[row limiting clause].
  • → development/databases/SQLite has the → development/databases/SQLite/sql/select/limit[limit clause].
  • Apparently, → development/databases/MySQL[MySQL] also comes with a limit clause.
  • → development/databases/SQL-Server has the → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql/select/top-n[top n clause].

sa:
  → development/databases/SQL/select[SQL: select statements]
